t-pgsql (3.5.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bug fixes:
    - Fixed macOS awk compatibility (regex negation syntax)
    - Fixed batch command silent exit with set -e
    - Fixed defaults not being applied to jobs (force, output, exclude_data)
  * Improvements:
    - Added get_job_value() for defaults fallback in job config
    - Jobs now properly inherit defaults section values
    - Added buffer/compression defaults support in YAML config

 -- Asim Atasert <asimatasert@outlook.com>  Tue, 07 Jan 2026 14:00:00 +0300

t-pgsql (3.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New features:
    - Streaming mode (--stream): Direct pipe clone without temp files
    - Parallel batch execution (--parallel N)
    - Job filtering (--only, --exclude)
    - Batch summary notifications (--notify-summary)
    - Config file support (--config)
    - Health checks before operations (--health-check)
    - GFS retention policy (--retention)
    - Data masking after restore (--mask)
  * Documentation updates
  * Added Fish shell completion
  * Added man page

 -- Asim Atasert <asimatasert@outlook.com>  Mon, 06 Jan 2026 12:00:00 +0300

t-pgsql (3.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Added profile-based job configuration in jobs.yaml
  * Enhanced exclude-data option to support schema.* wildcard

 -- Asim Atasert <asimatasert@outlook.com>  Sat, 04 Jan 2026 12:00:00 +0300

t-pgsql (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Features:
    - Dump: Backup from local or remote database
    - Restore: Restore backup to local or remote database
    - Clone: Single command dump + restore
    - Fetch: Download existing dump from remote
    - Batch: Run multiple jobs sequentially
    - SSH tunnel support
    - Password file support

 -- Asim Atasert <asimatasert@outlook.com>  Tue, 31 Dec 2024 12:00:00 +0300
